### Wiki weapon items (`tags: weapon`)

On wiki item pages tagged **`weapon`**, add a 5e-style stat block after the opening lore paragraph. Use the same `<div class="stat-block">` wrapper as NPC stats. Reference: `anasthetic-scalpel.textile`, `the-gonne.textile`, `the-gladius.textile`.

**Skeleton:**

```html
<div class="stat-block">
<h3>Item name</h3>
<p><em>Weapon category (e.g. martial melee weapon, martial ranged weapon)</em></p>
<p><strong>Damage</strong> …<br>
<strong>Properties</strong> …</p>
<hr>
<p><strong>Rarity</strong> …<br>
<strong>Attunement</strong> …</p>
<hr>
<p><strong>Special property.</strong> …</p>
</div>
```

- **Magic weapons** — state rarity and attunement; use *Weapon (type), rarity* on the type line when helpful.
- **Mundane weapons** — omit rarity; note origin (e.g. Anathemist) in prose or a trait.
- **Special properties** — one `<p><strong>Name.</strong> …</p>` per ability; match canon from sessions or NPC stat blocks where the item already appeared.
- Do not duplicate inner `<h3>` titles when the page title is already the item name (same rule as faction `h3.` stat blocks).

### Founder symbolic items (GM stat blocks)

The eight House regalia (plus [[The Red Mourning | The Red Mourning]] for Samhain) are **artifact**-tier items. Each has its own wiki page with **`op_gm_only: true`** (whole page GM-only on OP). Stat blocks live in each page's `GM_INFO` block. Tie abilities to the founder's curse and House philosophy; include at least one **Detrimental** property reflecting the millennium-long affliction. Personal founder gear that is not regalia (e.g. [[Swordbreaker | Swordbreaker]]) uses **`op_gm_only: true`** as well. Reference: `the-gladius.textile`, `the-cel-s.textile`, `the-amulet-of-stars.textile`.

### Wiki encounter building (multi-stat factions)

On wiki pages with faction combat stats (e.g. `anathemists.textile`, `the-black-cats.textile`), use **`h2. Encounter building`** in the GM block:

1. Short intro (multiplier reminder).
2. **Adjusted XP threshold matrix** — party of seven, levels 3–10, Easy / Medium / Hard / Deadly (DMG p. 82 per-character thresholds × 7).
3. **Composition table** — `| Composition | Adjusted XP |` for this faction’s example mixes, **sorted ascending by adjusted XP**.
4. **`h3.` per variant** — one-line blurb, then `<div class="stat-block">` without an inner `<h3>` title.

Single-NPC character pages keep the name inside `.stat-block` (see Pthul).

**Threshold matrix (copy when adding a composition table):**

| Level | Easy | Medium | Hard | Deadly |
